        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We propose to map in CO(J=1-0) the extended RC emission of the cooling core
cluster A2029 , at z=0.076. To cover an area 118 x 135 arcsec wide (corresponding
to 168 x 193 kpc) a 23 pointings (spaced by half primary beam) mosaic 
is requested.

Requested sensitivity: Assuming, at first order, that the RC-CO relation holds
in cluster central regions, we determined from the radio continuum brightness,
the expected CO brightness for the target A2029 to be ~1.7e9 Jy/sterad
km/s. Assuming a synthesized beam of 5.00 arcsec and a velocity width of 200
km/s, we estimate a line peak of ~5.6 mJy/beam. To detect this signal at least 5
sigma level in a channel width of 10 km/s, enough to resolve the line, we request 
a rms of 1 mJy/beam. 
The ALMA OT estimates a total time for the 23 pointings mosaic of ~5.5 hours. 

Correlator setup: We ask for the Frequency Division Mode of the correlator in
dual polarization (1875 MHz bandwidth) providing a spectral resolution more than 
sufficient for our purposes. 
To decrease the data rate we use a spectral average of a factor of 2,
leading to a resolution of ~3.16 km/s. 
Smoothing the channels to 10 km/s will
allow us to accurately sample the line, expected to be ~200 km/s wide. We used
10 km/s to calculate the time needed to reach the required sensitivity. We
centered the first baseband at the CO(1-0) frequency, and we located the
remaining baseband to cover the entire band, in order to estimate the continuum.</prj:justificationText>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
